# git-cross Mixed Prefix Example
# This example demonstrates that replay is agnostic to the command prefix.
# 'cross' is the standard, portable prefix.
# 'git cross' can be used if you have the git alias configured.
# 'just cross' can be used if you have 'just' installed.

# 1. Standard portable prefix (Recommended)
cross use portable https://github.com/epcim/git-cross.git

# 2. Git alias prefix (Requires 'git config --global alias.cross ...')
git cross use git-aliased https://github.com/epcim/git-cross.git

# 3. Just implementation prefix (Requires 'just' in PATH)
just cross use just-impl https://github.com/epcim/git-cross.git

# 4. Mixed patches
cross patch portable:README.md vendor/docs/readme-portable.md
git cross patch git-aliased:LICENSE vendor/docs/license-git.md
just cross patch just-impl:AGENTS.md vendor/docs/agents-just.md

# 5. Post-patching hooks
cross exec "echo 'Mixed replay completed successfully!'"
